**Language/Version**: Python 3.11 (project targets Python 3.12 in docs; implement on 3.11+ compatible)
**Primary Dependencies**: requests, click, pydantic (optional for validation), tenacity (already used), ldap3 (already used for DN parsing)
**Storage**: None persistent — operations performed against the remote XC API; transient local state in memory and failure reports written to disk (CSV or JSON)
**Testing**: pytest (existing tests), click.testing for CLI; unit tests for GroupSyncService and integration-like dry-run tests
**Target Platform**: macOS/Linux environments where CLI is run; CI runs in Linux (GitHub Actions)
**Project Type**: CLI service library (Python package in `src/`)
**Performance Goals**: Handle CSVs up to tens of thousands of rows; implement batching and rate-limiting for very large imports (deferred to Phase 2)
**Constraints**: External API rate limits and private dependencies (some packages may not be resolvable by pip-audit)
**Scale/Scope**: Initial goal: safely process CSV files up to 50k rows with retries; for larger scale, introduce chunking/batching in Phase 2

